 E, F
\varphi : E \to F 
\sigma (E, E^*) 
\varepsilon > 0 
 x \in V \Rightarrow \| \varphi(x) \| < \varepsilon 
f_i \in E^* \forall i 
 V  = \lbrace x \in E \mid \| \langle f_i , x \rangle \| < \delta \ \forall i = 1, 2, \dots , n \rbrace 
M =  \lbrace x \in E \mid \langle f_i , x \rangle = 0 \forall i =1, 2,\dots n \rbrace 
 \varphi (x)=0 \ \forall x \in M 
 M \subseteq \text{ Ker }\varphi 
x \in M
\langle f_i,x\rangle = 0
i
t\cdot x \in V
t\in \mathbb{K}
\lVert \varphi(t\cdot x)\rVert = \lVert t\cdot\varphi(x)\rVert = \lvert t\rvert\cdot \lVert \varphi(x)\rVert \leqslant \varepsilon
t\in\mathbb{K}
\varphi(y) \neq 0
t = \frac{\varepsilon+1}{\lVert\varphi(y)\rVert}
y \notin M
